# Component Organization Guide

## Directory Structure

Components are organized by feature and role:

```
src/components/
├── auth/                    # Authentication components
├── dashboard/               # Single dashboard with role-based content
├── sidebar/                 # Role-specific navigation
├── activePentests/          # Pentest management
├── vulenerabilityReports/   # Vulnerability system
├── ui/                      # Shared UI components
└── shared/                  # Cross-role components
```

## Component Patterns

### Single Component with Role Logic
Prefer single components with conditional rendering over separate role-specific components:

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Single component with role logic
function Dashboard() {
  const { isAdmin, isPentester, isClient } = useUser();
  
  return (
    <div>
      {isAdmin() && <AdminMetrics />}
      {isPentester() && <PentesterMetrics />}
      {isClient() && <ClientMetrics />}
      
      {/* Shared components */}
      <Activities />
    </div>
  );
}

// ❌ Avoid: Separate components for each role
// AdminDashboard, PentesterDashboard, ClientDashboard
```

### Shared Components with Role Awareness
Components used across roles should be role-aware:

```typescript
// Example: Activities component
function Activities() {
  const { isPentester, isClient } = useUser();
  
  const endpoint = isClient() 
    ? '/client/latest-activities'
    : isPentester() 
      ? '/pentester/latest-activities'
      : '/admin/latest-activities';
  
  const { data } = useQuery(['activities', role], () => 
    axiosInstance.get(endpoint)
  );
}
```

### Permission-Based Action Buttons
Action buttons should be conditionally rendered based on permissions:

```typescript
// Example from vulnerability view
{isReporter() && isPentester() && (
  <Button onClick={() => navigate(`/edit`)}>
    <Edit /> Edit
  </Button>
)}

{!isPentester() && !isClient() && (
  <Button onClick={() => deleteVulnerability()}>
    <Trash2 /> Delete
  </Button>
)}
```

